PN,31604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1776942175
OL,3,CHow UV rays cause sunburn - and why
OL,4,Csun cream still matters in spring
OL,6,FUV radiation damages skin cell DNA,
OL,7,Fand your immune system responds with
OL,8,Fredness, heat, swelling and pain.
OL,10,FIn more severe cases, you can get
OL,11,Fblistering, fever, chills, or
OL,12,Fdehydration - it's essentially a mild
OL,13,Fradiation injury.
OL,15,FThe bigger concern is what repeated or
OL,16,Fsevere sunburns do over time.
OL,18,FEach burn increases cumulative DNA
OL,19,Fdamage in skin cells.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1776942175
OL,3,CHow UV rays cause sunburn - and why
OL,4,Csun cream still matters in spring
OL,6,FYour body can repair some of it, but
OL,7,Fnot always perfectly and that raises
OL,8,Fthe risk of skin cancer - one of the
OL,9,FUK's most common cancers and also one
OL,10,Fof the most preventable.
OL,12,FCan sunshine be beneficial?
OL,14,FYes, it is good for us, but the key
OL,15,Fhere is controlled moderation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
