OL,3,CHow UV rays cause sunburn - and why
OL,4,Csun cream still matters in spring
OL,6,FThis will be particularly true towards
OL,7,Fthe east coast over the next few days;
OL,8,Fa cold east to northeasterly wind will
OL,9,Fmake it feel cold enough for coats but
OL,10,Fthe strength of the sun - and
OL,11,Ftherefore the risk of burning - will
OL,12,Fbe just as great in the east as it is
OL,13,Facross more sheltered western areas
OL,14,Fwhere temperatures rise to 21C.
OL,16,FWill suncream stop me from getting a
OL,17,Ftan?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1776942175
OL,3,CHow UV rays cause sunburn - and why
OL,4,Csun cream still matters in spring
OL,6,FNo, it just happens more slowly and
OL,7,Fusually more safely as you're much
OL,8,Fless likely to burn, which is the real
OL,9,Fdamage you want to avoid.
OL,11,FWhat do the experts say?
OL,13,FIn his many years of practice, Mr
OL,14,FGurjinderpal Singh Pahal, Consultant
OL,15,FPlastic & Reconstructive Surgeon and
OL,16,FLead Clinician at The Royal London
OL,17,FHospital, said most of the melanomas
OL,18,Fhe saw and removed were "entirely
OL,19,Fpreventable".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
