PN,31610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1776942175
OL,3,CHow UV rays cause sunburn - and why
OL,4,Csun cream still matters in spring
OL,6,F"The sun accumulates its damage
OL,7,Fsilently, year after year, deep in the
OL,8,FDNA of your skin cells, long before
OL,9,Fanything is visible to the naked eye.
OL,11,F"Ultraviolet radiation is, without
OL,12,Fquestion, the most pervasive and
OL,13,Funderestimated carcinogen in our daily
OL,14,Flives. None of my patients, looking
OL,15,Fback, have ever wished they'd worn
OL,16,Fless sunscreen.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1776942175
OL,3,CHow UV rays cause sunburn - and why
OL,4,Csun cream still matters in spring
OL,6,F"My advice is unequivocal ` broad-
OL,7,Fspectrum SPF 50, every morning, every
OL,8,Fseason, regardless of cloud cover. The
OL,9,Ftan fades in a fortnight; the damage,
OL,10,FI'm afraid, is rather more permanent.
OL,11,FThe bottom line is that the skin
OL,12,Fremembers everything, and you should
OL,13,Fdo whatever you can to protect it"
